<p itemprop="description">A lead network architect uses their expert knowledge and experience to direct work addressing high level and complex network scenarios. They support and lead other network architects, set strategic direction, and champion network architecture across the organisation.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and direct the application of network architectural principles, methods, and tools across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish network architecture strategy and standards across the entire organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide expert consultancy on complex network transformation challenges</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead cross-organisational initiatives and major network architecture programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop the network architecture capability and community</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with senior leadership to align network architecture with organisational strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Champion network architecture best practices and maturity across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in external network architecture communities and forums</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive digital transformation through innovative network solutions</li>
    </ul>
</section>

